Digging further, `get_swap_device` checks that `si` is non-NULL after extracting the swap info using `swp_swap_info(entry)`. The `__swap_entry_to_info(entry)` function just extracts from `swap_info[type]`. So no bounds checking here either! That's the part that is concerning. It assumes the entry is valid. We need to be sure that the pinning mechanism in uswsusp guarantees the validity of the `entry` throughout the free operation. We should verify that the hibernation code ensures the entry is valid.


